---
1.git init
2.git add .
3.git status
4.git commit -m "push for full project"
5.git branch -M main (renaming branch)
6.git remote add origin https://github.com/Richa444/Academy3.git
7.git push -u origin master
8.rm -rf .git (to help git to untrack your repo)
9. rm -rf your_virtualenv_directory(to remove a directory in droplet)
10 git clone -b <branch_name> <repository_url> (clone data from right branch)


-----
git remote -v(to see how many branches you have)
git remote remove origin( you should delete all origins in case if problem is while pushing the code)
------------------------
(extra commands)
1.git remote add origin git remote set-url origin 
2.git checkout -b dev  (creates new branch name dev)

